        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Rochester</placeName>, <date>Feb 26th 5627</date></p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is now a considerable<lb/> long time that I have not
                contrib<lb/>uted any thing to your valuable<lb/> Organ for the elaboration of
                Judaism.<lb/> Having now delivered last<lb/>
                <date>Sabbath-day</date> a Sermon, which<lb/> I think will make particul-<lb/>arly
                by the many of your readers<lb/> at the <placeName>South</placeName> a good
                impression<lb/> I take the liberty of sending you<lb/> a copy thereof, which I
                hope<lb/> you may find not unworthy to<lb/> insert in your dignified Journal<lb/> as
                it certainly will make <add>קדוש השם</add><lb/> for it shows the high &amp;
                incompar<lb/>able moral of our holy religion</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Wishing that these lines may<lb/> find you by restored health<lb/> &amp; in the full
                enjoyment of life,<lb/> so that you may able to work<lb/> many years for <add>כרם ד'
                    צבאות</add><lb/> I remain Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Your</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)"><sic>faithfull</sic> &amp; sincere friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">A. Guinzburg</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P.S. There where I have made<lb/> a lead-pencil mark, it ought<lb/> to be:</p>
            <p>“and which we therefore <hi rend="underline">should</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">not</hi> overhear.”</p>
        </body>
    </text>
